===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# [[at|At]] [[no]] [[time]]; on no [[occasion]]; in no [[circumstance]].
#: ''I finally finished, and I '''never''' want to do that again.''
#: ''I repeated the test a hundred times, and '''never''' saw a positive result.''
#: ''I will '''never''' tell.''
#* '''1634''', [[w:William Shakespeare|William Shakespeare]], [[w:John Fletcher|John Fletcher]], ''[[s:The Two Noble Kinsmen/Act 2/Scene 4|The Two Noble Kinsmen]]'', Act 2, Scene 4,
#*: Why should I love this Gentleman? Tis odds / He '''never''' will affect me;
#* '''1908''', [[w:Lucy Maud Montgomery|Lucy Maud Montgomery]], ''[[s:Anne of Green Gables/Chapter XXI|Anne of Green Gables]]'', Chapter XXI: A New Departure in Flavorings,
#*: "I '''never''' thought you were so fond of Mr. Phillips that you'd require two handkerchiefs to dry your tears just because he was going away," said Marilla.
#* '''1919''', B. G. Jefferis, J. L. Nichols, ''[[s:Searchlights on Health/Sensible Rules for the Nurse|Searchlights on Health: Sensible Rules for the Nurse]]'',
#*: '''Never''' speak of the symptoms of your patient in his presence, unless questioned by the doctor, whose orders you are always to obey ''implicitly''.
# Not at any [[other]] time; not on any other occasion; not [[previously]].
#* '''1601''' Novenber 30, [[w:Elizabeth I of England|Elizabeth I of England]], ''[[s:Elizabeth I's Farewell Speech|Elizabeth I's Farewell Speech]]'',
#*: There is no jewel, be it of '''never''' so rich a price, which I set before this jewel: I mean your love.
#* '''1813''', [[w:Jane Austen|Jane Austen]], ''[[s:Pride and Prejudice/Chapter 4|Pride and Prejudice]]'', Chapter 4,
#*: "He is just what a young man ought to be," said she, "sensible, good-humoured, lively; and I '''never''' saw such happy manners!--so much ease, with such perfect good breeding!"
#* '''1908''', [[w:Lucy Maud Montgomery|Lucy Maud Montgomery]], ''[[s:Anne of Green Gables/Chapter XIII|Anne of Green Gables]]'', Chapter XIII: The Delights of Anticipation,
#*: I '''never''' saw such an infatuated man.
# {{colloquial}} Negative particle (''used to negate verbs in the simple past tense; also used [[absolutely]]'').
#: ''The police say I stole the car, but I '''never''' did it.''
#: ''You said you were going to mow the lawn today.'' – ''I '''never'''!''<!--example of "never" used absolutely in this sense-->

